column12: Notes

column8: [Andre Gee, Elias Leight, Caitlin White, Steven Hyden, Aaron Williams]
column12: Additional Authors (listed after initial correct author) are from the by-lines of linked articles that include a by-line caption

column8: [Usa Today, Charles Ventura, Am Pdt November]
column12: One listed “author” (the parent company of the site) is skipped and a chunk of the date is picked up as an additional author

column11: Mariah Noble, Bob Mims, Rachel Piper

column12: This article is in Arabic. Newspaper just returns an empty array. Goose panics and returns an error.
Meta tag and h5 rel property present to indicate the author. DiffBot gives authorURL too.

Newspaper here relies on the meta author tag, which specifies Abc News. It ignores a clear “by” at the head of the article, in a div with the properties rel and class = “author”. DiffBot gets this one right, just lower cases it.
This is a 404 page. No erroneous authors detected, though no meta author tag present, which may have resulted in a mistaken result.
A <meta property=“article:author”> is present in this success

column11: Kit Rees and Julien Ponthus, Reuters
column12:
<Attribute name="author">By Kit Rees and Julien Ponthus,</Attribute> in <PageMap><DataObject> ignored. Clear by-line. Also <div class="author-name">
DiffBot gets an image author attribution but no author [Reuters Staff].
Some author class names but no explicit meta tag, or “by”. Author URL detected.
“Hours Ago” clearly not a name. It seems that dates are a common mistake. DiffBot avoids the trap of “Hours Ago”.
Some capitalization errors but correct from both libraries. Meta author tag.
Auto-capitalization but correct for one library. No meta tags to rely on except a class name with multiple other words and underscores.
DiffBot gets “AP” where neither of the others do. <meta name="parsely-author" content=“AP">

column8: [Kira Davis, Neil Stevens, Kimberly Ross, Jon Street, Posted At Am On November, Amelia Hamilton, Sarah Lee, Brad Slager, Jim Jamitis, Caleb Howe]
column12: By-lines of linked articles picked up. Correct one not first.
“Min Read” is from “4 Min Read” listed in the same location as the author.
Correctly returns none.
Missed despite “by” line.
Feed URL.Correctly no authors.
Linked article by-lines misidentified again

column8: [View All Posts Joel D Hirst, Joel D, Posted On]
column12: Links incorrectly identified as authors e.g. “View All Posts”. Meta tags seem to be relied on as there is no by-line but just a blog author.
